description:
This is my most advanced batch file OS and made totally by me. 

---Update 2016---
If you want to help make Log OS better, download the beta version here: https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B_igBtlvxUYpQUg2MVZ1Q0VURjQ/view?usp=sharing
Stable (normal) download link : https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B_igBtlvxUYpZXc2SjBwUzJYMHM/view?usp=sharing
If you'd like to customize the bootscreen of Log OS, use this link:https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B_igBtlvxUYpT1lxSUVVblk0a0k/view?usp=sharing
If you'd want to have pre-alpha access to LogOS ver. 3.0, check this link:https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B_igBtlvxUYpWHM2NUZQQ3Q4am8/view?usp=sharing

All mentioned links should work now. But if you find any broken links, tell me so I can fix them.
P.S. I didn't bother using short URLs anymore. Just the direct URL, so you can trust it.

chapters.title: Refreshing system means checking for empty variables in system settings and replaces settings if neccessary. This is very advanced system.
Switching user accounts quickly in start screen (switch username)
This will close batch file by saving session to settings.
"Type" is application that can show contents of a text file.
You can also use recovery console. Here's how you can boot to it.

comments.text:
Something new is coming soon!

Log OS 2.9 (yes, it is not 3.0 yet)

What it will have?
 - New apps (e.g. ASCII viewer and Sound player)
 - New start screen interface (with auto updating clock)
 - New login screen
 - Smart variable management (real cache cleaning)
 - New bootscreen with animation
 - New firmware
 - OTA (Over The Air ie internet based update) and local system update support
 - Widescreen support
 - True hibernate (it actually saves session)
 - New error screens and color system
 - BIOS setup?

In 3.0 I'll probably do:
 - Mouse UI
 - Unlimited user accounts
 - Embedded edition
 - Website to download it
